These are capabilities that may have been lost when we switched over
to Tscroll.


   SCREEN HELP key (see menu status line) brings up text screen with short
      descriptions of the menu choices.
 COPY key (help or text status line) copies text into a file in your 
      login directory.
     BACK UP key (see status line) moves you to previous menu you selected
      (Ctrl-z also works).
   REFRESH key (see status line) redraws the screen (useful for removing
      system notice messages).
   PRINT SCREEN key (see status line) takes a snap of the current screen 
      and prints it on the Talaris 1590LN in CDAC Room 156.
   REPORT key (see status line) puts you into an editor to compose a 
      problem report or comment for the CGIS support person.
